newsArray.title: Jos Buttler becomes 5th cricketer in history to register massive milestone in white-ball cricket
newsArray.description: Jos Buttler may have fallen cheaply in the second T20I against New Zealand, managing just four runs, but his lone boundary at the Hagley Oval in Christchurch was enough to etch his name into the record books. With that shot, Buttler became only the fifth player in history to smash 350 or more boundaries in both ODIs and T20Is. He joins an elite group featuring Rohit Sharma, Virat Kohli, Paul Stirling, and Babar Azam.
